This is the first budget in the city's history that will be tabled by a coalition government. JOHANNESBURG - Finance MMC Rabelani Dagada will table the City of Johannesburg s budget for the 2017/2018 financial year on Tuesday which will focus on the advancement of communities.This is the first budget in the city's history that will be tabled by a coalition government.Dagada will outline the city's budget and allocation of funds to projects, programmes and initiatives.The City's Luyanda Mfeka says: The MMC will also layout how the tariff increases - which have already been published - will be utilised to improve service delivery in the city, manage our infrastructure backlog of over R170 billion and deliver the change which this city voted for. (Edited by Shimoney Regter)